Bishop David Oyedepo, the overseer of Living Faith Church (Winners Chapel), has called on Nigerians to come together and fight against  the Hate Speech Bill. Oyedepo made this call at the church’s annual event themed Shiloh 2019 which commenced on Monday. READ ALSO:  Most problems at homes are caused by wives’ … – Oyedepo According to Oyedepo, “Hate speech is one of the most crazy idea ever. He stated, “So if you are wrong, they shouldn’t say you are wrong? If the road is bad, they cannot say the road is bad? You cannot silence a prophet. “Are we going forward or backward as a nation? Are the roads better? So why are you not talking? Let’s join hands together and evil shall not prevail,” he asked. “They are not hanging killers and they want to hang speakers. That bill is dead on arrival,”  he stressed.